---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Web Development — Jacob A. Torres"
  description="Web development projects by Jacob A. Torres."
>
  <h1>Web Development</h1>

  <p>
    I'm skilled in accessible UI development with HTML, CSS, and
    JavaScript/TypeScript, with experience building web applications using
    Django and Flask. Below are some of my web development projects, including
    deployed sites you can visit live.
  </p>

  <h2>Projects</h2>

  <ul class="project-list" aria-label="Web development projects">
    <li class="project-card">
      <span class="tag">Web Development</span>
      <h3>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/jacob-torres/story-builder"
          rel="external noopener"
          aria-label="Story Builder on GitHub (opens in new tab)"
        >
          Story Builder
        </a>
      </h3>
      <p>
        A web application for collaboratively writing and organizing short
        fiction and stories.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Deployed Sites</h2>

  <ul class="project-list" aria-label="Deployed web development sites">
    <li class="project-card">
      <span class="tag">Live Site</span>
      <h3>
        <a
          href="https://jacob-torres.github.io/Denver-Streets"
          rel="external noopener"
          aria-label="Denver Street Guide (opens in new tab)"
        >
          Denver Street Guide
        </a>
      </h3>
      <p>
        An operations and maintenance street reference guide for the Denver
        metro area.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="project-card">
      <span class="tag">Live Site</span>
      <h3>
        <a
          href="https://denver-nav.onrender.com"
          rel="external noopener"
          aria-label="Accessible Denver Navigation App (opens in new tab)"
        >
          Accessible Denver Navigation App
        </a>
      </h3>
      <p>
        An accessible navigation application for getting around the Denver
        metro area.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
